OL,3,CCouncil worker 'stole from the people
OL,4,Cof this city' in #40,000 plot
OL,6,FDefending, Kate Morley said: "Owen is
OL,7,F36, has never acted dishonestly
OL,8,Fpreviously, and always prided himself
OL,9,Fon his strong character. That came
OL,10,Fcrashing down following the unexpected
OL,11,Fdeath of his friend.
OL,13,F"He couldn't cope, then turned to
OL,14,Falcohol and cocaine to numb the pain
OL,15,Fand it spiralled out of control.
OL,17,F"Living alone at the time, he got
OL,18,Fhimself into unmanageable debt and
OL,19,Faccrued addictions along the way. It
OL,20,Fwas obvious self destructive
OL,21,Fbehaviour, a cry for help.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
